IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: WORKMONEY IS DEDICATED TO LOWERING COSTS AND RAISING INCOMES FOR ALL AMERICANS.
IRS990.MissionDesc: WORKMONEY IS DEDICATED TO LOWERING COSTS AND RAISING INCOMES FOR ALL AMERICANS, MAKING LIFE MORE AFFORDABLE AND FAMILIES MORE ECONOMICALLY SECURE.
IRS990.Desc: OUTREACH: WORKMONEY COMMUNICATED WITH MILLIONS OF FINANCIALLY STRUGGLING, HARD-TO-REACH AMERICANS, DELIVERING VALUABLE REAL-TIME INFORMATION TO HELP THEM BETTER WEATHER FINANCIAL CHALLENGES. WORKMONEY PROVIDED INFORMATION ACROSS A RANGE OF COMMUNICATION CHANNELS TO HELP AMERICANS NAVIGATE THE ECONOMIC CRISIS CAUSED BY THE COVID-19 PANDEMIC, INCLUDING INFORMATION ON TAX CREDITS, STIMULUS PROGRAMS, AND OTHER BENEFIT PROGRAMS AND SERVICES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: EDUCATION: WORKMONEY PROVIDED INFORMATION TO SUBSCRIBERS TO HELP THEM NAVIGATE COMPLEX FINANCIAL PROGRAMS AND SERVICES, TO MATERIALLY IMPROVE THEIR FINANCIAL WELL-BEING. WORKMONEY HELD PERSONAL CONVERSATIONS WITH AMERICAN FAMILIES ABOUT ECONOMIC TOOLS AND THEIR IMPACT ON THEIR LIVES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: ADVOCACY: WORKMONEY EDUCATED DECISION-MAKERS ON THE NEEDS OF WORKING AMERICANS. THIS WORK INCLUDED CONDUCTING POLICY RESEARCH AND ANALYSIS AND SUPPORTING POLICIES THAT HELP RAISE INCOMES AND LOWER COSTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION COMMUNICATED WITH AMERICANS VIA SMS MESSAGING, PHONE CALLS, AND EMAIL TO SUPPORT AND OPPOSE CANDIDATES IN FEDERAL AND STATE ELECTIONS.

THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE HAS DETERMINED THAT THE ORGANIZATION IS DESCRIBED IN SECTION 501(C)(4) OF THE CODE AND, ACCORDINGLY, IS GENERALLY EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES UNDER THE PROVISION OF SECTION 501(A) OF THE CODE. HOWEVER, CERTAIN ACTIVITIES NOT DIRECTLY RELATED TO THE ORGANIZATION'S TAX-EXEMPT PURPOSES ARE NOT EXEMPT AND ARE SUBJECT TO FEDERAL INCOME TAXES. THE ORGANIZATION RECOGNIZES THE TAX BENEFIT FROM UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS ONLY IF IT IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT THAT THE TAX POSITIONS WILL BE SUSTAINED ON EXAMINATION BY THE TAX AUTHORITIES, BASED ON THE TECHNICAL MERITS OF THE POSITION. THE TAX BENEFIT IS MEASURED BASED ON THE LARGEST BENEFIT THAT HAS A GREATER THAN 50% LIKELIHOOD OF BEING REALIZED UPON ULTIMATE SETTLEMENT. THE ORGANIZATION RECOGNIZES INTEREST AND PENALTIES, IF ANY, RELATED TO INCOME TAX MATTERS IN FEDERAL TAX EXPENSE. THE ORGANIZATION HAD NO UNRECOGNIZED TAX BENEFITS AT DECEMBER 31, 2022. THE ORGANIZATION FILES AN EXEMPT ORGANIZATION RETURN WITH THE U.S. FEDERAL AND WISCONSIN JURISDICTIONS.

IN 2021 THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS OF WORKMONEY, INC. HELD A SPECIAL MEETING. CARRIE JOY GRIMES, DIRECTOR OF THE ORGANIZATION, DID NOT ATTEND THE EXECUTIVE SESSION PORTION OF THE MEETING AT WHICH THE COMPENSATION OF THE CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER WAS REVIEWED AND APPROVED. AN ANNUAL SALARY AND ASSOCIATED EMPLOYEE BENEFITS WERE APPROVED, PURSUANT TO THE DEFINITION OF REASONABLE COMPENSATION UNDER INTERNAL REVENUE CODE SECTION 162. THE 2020 REGIONAL PAY NON-PROFIT REPORT PROVIDED THE BASIS FOR THE DETERMINED REASONABLE COMPENSATION. PURSUANT TO WORKMONEY'S CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, CARRIE JOY GRIMES DID NOT CONSENT TO THIS RESOLUTION.
